## Refactor

The genuine repeated code had **already been extracted once** by the L1/L2/L3 debriefs and lives in `legs.py`:
- `clone_after` — fresh-clone-then-replay
- `_reach_bfs` — movement flood, one clone/edge, position dedup (shared by `_move_explore` and `fast_reach`)
- `_use_macros` — walk-to-reachable-tile-then-USE successor expansion (shared by both planners)
- `plan_and_commit` — the "plan on a clone, commit on the real env" higher-order wrapper

